 Port Elizabeth police early on Friday morning arrested a 50-year-old man for being in possession of an unlicensed firearm. According to a police spokesperson, Captain Andre Beetge, the Motherwell Operational Command Centre and Crime Intelligence arrested the man in Zwide. “This followed after information was received and the suspect was found with a 9mm pistol and 11 rounds of ammunition at his home in Khwatsha Street, Zwide, at 02:00 this morning,” he added. “He will appear before the New Brighton Magistrate’s Court on Monday 9 April.”  